From 4f37f56bf7813c20fe24954bf5481bd3d5638a48 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 16:24:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] macOS 10.6 SDK and GCC 14 compatibility fixes for Cocoa
 GUI

Core:
- ValueUtil.h: Rename 'id' member to 'id_' to avoid Objective-C keyword conflict

CtrlCore:
- CocoMM.h: Add macOS 10.6 SDK compatibility defines for modern constant names
            (NSEventModifierFlag*, NSWindowStyleMask*, NSControlStateValue*, etc.)
            Add NSColorToCGColor() helper function for 10.6 (no .CGColor property)
- CocoApp.mm: Convert for-in loops to traditional C loops for GCC compatibility
              Make Apple blocks conditional on __clang__ or __BLOCKS__
              Replace property dot syntax with message syntax for NSEvent
              Use respondsToSelector for backingScaleFactor (10.7+)
- CocoClip.mm: Replace lambda with ObjC method for GCC compatibility
- CocoProc.mm: Convert for-in loops and FindMatch lambda to traditional loops

CtrlLib:
- ChCocoMM.mm: Major rewrite removing lambdas and @available checks
               Replace Upp::decode() with switch statements
               Use NSColorToCGColor() helper for color conversion
               Convert property syntax to message syntax

Draw:
- FontCoco.mm: Add kCTFontOrientationHorizontal compatibility define

ide/Builders:
- Cocoa.cpp: Use MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET for Info.plist LSMinimumSystemVersion
             Default to 10.6 for maximum compatibility

These fixes enable building on macOS 10.6 SDK with GCC 14 (no blocks, no @available).
